<br>
If you want to know why Hitler gained so much power you have to check all the circumstances.  First what France and England did to them, with Americans headed by Woodrow Wilson sitting by watching, made for some bitter bitter people.  I mean people listen they did not even let Germany come to the peace conference they were handed a peace of paper which was not the 14 points that they surrendered under.  So they are already ticked off.  Now comes where the hatred toward the Jews comes in.  No not all Jews did this and I am not saying that it gives the Germans a right to hate but if you look all throughout history you will find that Jewish people prosper.  The Jews of Germany, those living there and ones who moved there after WWI, prospered and much of the time it was due to shrewd bargaining and manipulation of the people.  So in this sense when you are getting beat on and beat on you will strike back and sometimes you hit someone that just has something in common with those who were hitting you.  As for how did Hitler come to power himself well he was very charismatic and was a war hero in himself for the Germans.  He attemped one hostile takeover and the government and was quickly thrown into jail for it.  During his jail time he did a lot of writing and reading.  When he left office he decided to come to power through legal means.  He was elected to Prime Minister I believe and was then granted complete rulership when he asked for it.  <br>
<br>
Why did Hitler hate the Jews is another question  Here is the historical answer.<br>
<br>
Three reasons<br>
1.  Hitler is half Jew himself.  His father was Jewish his mother German.  His father beat his mother and Hitler hated him for it.<br>
<br>
2.  The doctor that was unable to save Hitler's mother from a disease was Jewish and Hitler blamed the doctor for his mothers death.<br>
<br>
3.  Hitler was an aspiring artist.  He tried to join a Jewish Art School and was told he had no talent and decided that the Jewish people were discriminating against him.<br>
<br>
